      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-01-hemolysis-lab",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — laboratory bench study at 22°C, atmospheric pressure",
      "description": "Bench-top validation of CFD-predicted hemolysis index against experimental measurements using bovine blood at 22°C and standard atmospheric pressure (101.3 kPa). Five flow-speed operating points were tested. Predicted RH values agreed with measured values within ±8% across all points. No variation of ambient temperature, electromagnetic interference, or reduced-pressure conditions was introduced during testing. The validation dataset does not include operating points outside the 22°C, 1 atm baseline."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error study",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed on three systematically refined meshes (4.2M, 11.7M, and 31.4M cells). GCI for the hemolysis-relevant shear stress quantity of interest was below 2.1% on the medium mesh, confirming discretization error is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-solver-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical solver verification against manufactured solution",
      "description": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the Navier-Stokes solver kernel. Second-order spatial convergence confirmed. Residual norms below 1e-6 for all operating points. No solver-related errors identified."
    }
  ],
