      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation test conditions documented; key boundary conditions match simulation inputs within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Laboratory test conditions documented: 22°C, 101.3 kPa, bovine blood viscosity 3.2 mPa·s. Flow rates and rotational speeds controlled to within ±1% of nominal. Boundary conditions in the CFD model set to match measured laboratory values. The operating theatre deployment environment — which includes ambient temperatures of 18–26°C, potential EMI from electrosurgical units and patient monitoring equipment, and reduced ambient pressure at high-altitude facilities (as low as 85 kPa) — was not reproduced or bracketed in the validation test matrix. A single temperature condition (22°C) was used; no sensitivity to temperature, EMI, or reduced pressure was evaluated."
